HI EVERYONE, PLEASE SIGN & SHARE THIS PETITION TO URGE ADIDAS TO STOP MURDERING KANGAROOS FOR SHOES! Millions of kangaroos are brutally slaughtered each year, and their skins are used to create kangaroo leather, or k-leather, for products like shoes. Several companies have started to move away from using the skins of butchered kangaroos, and it is time that Adidas follows suit. Urge the CEO of Adidas to phase out kangaroo leather in its products! Kangaroo leather is primarily used to create soccer cleats. However, major brands Nike and Puma recently announced that they will no longer continue to use kangaroo leather to make their shoes, making it the perfect time to pressure other companies like Adidas to follow suit. This cruel industry leaves baby kangaroos, called joeys, left to starve to death after their mothers are killed because they are not useful, or they are killed by having their necks broken, decapitated, or bludgeoned. Their deaths are not included in the conservative estimate of the 2 million kangaroos who are slaughtered each year. Kangaroos also already face threats from habitat loss, bushfires, and severe drought that are all exacerbated by the ongoing climate crisis. Despite all of this, the massacre of kangaroos for commercial gain continues. The United States is currently the second-largest market for kangaroo leather. Don’t order adidas online. Customer service sucks. They shipped me my shoes I originally ordered but unfortunately the sizes run large, so I completed a size exchange. On the email it tells you as soon as the warehouse receives your order, they will send out the newly requested sizes. But what they don’t tell their customers is there is actually a 21 business day policy that allows them to hold the shoes to ‘review’ the shipment for potentially over a month. And in my case, months! I ordered shoes in October, completed the size exchange about a week later, had to call 3 times. First call was I placed after a few weeks had passed and I received no updated or communication that they even received my order. They informed about this 21 business day policy and that they were busy but it shouldn’t take that long. Second call placed well over a month later. Was informed that they were waiting on one shoe size to be fulfilled by the warehouse and that they hold the order until it becomes available. So I cancelled the shoe that was holding up the order so that the order could be sent out. Here we are in December with no refund for the shoe I cancelled or the shoes still pending for the size exchange. Still no communication made by them on my order. Third call was made to inquire about why I haven’t received my refund or order shipment. Apparently, the customer service only put in a request for a refund and not actually a refund. And they have no idea why my order wasn’t fulfilled. All they could do was cancel the full order. No offer to place my order again or work to send out what I paid for. Just a simple cancellation. Which I doubt I’ll even get since they didn’t process the refund I requested the first time. Don’t forget it also take up to 10 business days for me to receive a refund. So if I’m lucky I’ll get my money by the new year. I asked if my order could be escalated and the answer was no. They don’t have that option. They only can cancel. So beware!
